# Release & versioning guardrails (post-#970)

## When this rule attaches

**Situational** — globs above, semver bump / release doc work, or **`@release-versioning.mdc`**. **`release-publish-sequencing.mdc`** covers **tag → GitHub → Docker → Hub** choreography; **this rule** covers **authorization to bump** and **phantom-version prevention**.

## Two gates (ADR-0072 — Accepted)

| | **Commit gate** | **Release gate** |
|---|---|---|
| Question | May this code enter `main`? | May this version become stable? |
| Criterion | `check-all` / CI / pre-commit GREEN | Lab completão (#406) + operator FASE 3 |
| Vocabulary | **Never** call this "gate" alone — **local checks** / **CI** | **Gate** without qualifier = **this** |

**Green commit gate never authorizes removing `-beta`/`-rc` from `pyproject.toml`.**

## Version facts (ADR-0073 — Accepted)

- **`main` today:** **`1.7.4` STABLE** (release PR **#1024**); ADR-0073 **Accepted**; release gate **#406 CLOSED**.
- **#970:** premature stable bump/tag without release gate — corrected by **ADR-0072** + **#406**; **`1.7.4` is not VOID**.
- **Published stable:** tag **`v1.7.4`**, GitHub Release, Docker Hub **`1.7.4`** / **`latest`** — operator **release-ritual** post-merge (not agent-autonomous).
- **`1.7.5` does not exist.** Next dev line: **`1.8.0-beta`** (#772) **after** publish ritual completes.
- **Maturity octet** (0–127 beta · 128–199 rc · 200–255 release): **`[tool.databoar] maturity_build = 201`** side-channel — **never** in `[project] version` or About. See **`docs/VERSIONING.md`**.

## Distribution policy (pre-release vs stable)

| Channel | `-beta` / `-rc` | Stable (no suffix) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Git** (`main` / tags) | Yes — UAT/QA consume from git | Tag **`vX.Y.Z`** + GitHub Release |
| **Docker Hub** | **Never** push pre-release tags | **`X.Y.Z`** + **`latest`** after local smoke + scout |
| **PyPI** | **Never** | Stable only (#74 — post-1.7.4) |
| **Local image build** (smoke / scout) | OK — **do not push** | Required before Hub push |

Beta/rc builds stay **git-only** for external users; operators may build images locally without publishing.

## Agent must not

1. Bump to **stable** while a **`release-gate`** issue (e.g. **#406** successor) is **OPEN** without operator FASE 3.
2. Invent **`1.7.5`** / **`1.7.5-beta`** targeting.
3. Treat **verifiable** smoke hardening (#831) as **release gate passed**.
4. Tag, GitHub Release, or Docker Hub publish without operator **release-ritual** — pair with **`release-publish-sequencing.mdc`**.

## Machine guard

**`security/version_policy.yaml`** + **`tests/test_release_version_policy.py`** — run via **`check-all`**.

